  "prompt": "My heartrate is 60 beats per minute is that good or bad?",
  "response": "A heart rate of 60 beats per minute (bpm) can generally be considered healthy for most adults. The normal resting heart rate for adults ranges from 60 to 100 bpm. Factors that can influence your heart rate include:\n\n1. **Age**: Younger people tend to have higher heart rates.\n2. **Fitness level**: Athletes and individuals with high cardiovascular fitness often have lower resting heart rates.\n3. **Medication**: Some drugs can affect heart rate.\n4. **Emotions**: Stress or excitement can temporarily increase heart rate.\n5. **Body position**: Standing versus lying down can affect heart rate.\n6. **Hormones**: Thyroid-related hormones can influence heart rate.\n\nHowever, if you have any concerns about your heart rate or if you experience symptoms such as dizziness, shortness of breath, or palpitations, it's a good idea to consult a healthcare professional for personalized advice.",
